defs.name: CookieJar
defs.docs: A collection of cookies that tracks its modifications.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty cookie jar.

defs.name: get
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the `Cookie` inside this jar with the name
 `name`. If no such cookie exists, returns `None`.

defs.name: add_original
defs.docs:
Adds an "original" `cookie` to this jar. If an original cookie with the
 same name already exists, it is replaced with `cookie`. Cookies added
 with `add` take precedence and are not replaced by this method.

defs.name: add
defs.docs:
Adds `cookie` to this jar. If a cookie with the same name already
 exists, it is replaced with `cookie`.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes `cookie` from this jar. If an _original_ cookie with the same
 name as `cookie` is present in the jar, a _removal_ cookie will be
 present in the `delta` computation. To properly generate the removal
 cookie, `cookie` must contain the same `path` and `domain` as the cookie
 that was initially set.

defs.name: force_remove
defs.docs:
Removes `cookie` from this jar completely. This method differs from
 `remove` in that no delta cookie is created under any condition. Neither
 the `delta` nor `iter` methods will return a cookie that is removed
 using this method.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Removes all cookies from this cookie jar.

attributes.value:
deprecated(since = "0.7.0", note =
             "calling this method may not remove \
                 all cookies since the path and domain are not specified; use \
                 `remove` instead")

defs.name: delta
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over cookies that represent the changes to this jar
 over time. These cookies can be rendered directly as `Set-Cookie` header
 values to affect the changes made to this jar on the client.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over all of the cookies present in this jar.

defs.name: Delta
defs.docs: Iterator over the changes to a cookie jar.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: Iterator over all of the cookies in a jar.

defs.name: Strict
defs.docs: The "Strict" `SameSite` attribute.

defs.name: Lax
defs.docs: The "Lax" `SameSite` attribute.

defs.name: None
defs.docs: No `SameSite` attribute.

defs.name: SameSite
defs.docs: The `SameSite` cookie attribute.

defs.name: is_strict
defs.docs: Returns `true` if `self` is `SameSite::Strict` and `false` otherwise.

defs.name: is_lax
defs.docs: Returns `true` if `self` is `SameSite::Lax` and `false` otherwise.

defs.name: is_none
defs.docs: Returns `true` if `self` is `SameSite::None` and `false` otherwise.

defs.name: Cookie
defs.docs: Representation of an HTTP cookie.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn <N, V> (name: N, value: V) -> Cookie<'static>
defs.docs: Creates a new `Cookie` with the given name and value.

defs.name: named
defs.docs: Creates a new `Cookie` with the given name and an empty value.

defs.name: build
defs.value: fn <N, V> (name: N, value: V) -> CookieBuilder
defs.docs:
Creates a new `CookieBuilder` instance from the given key and value
 strings.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs:
Parses a `Cookie` from the given HTTP cookie header value string. Does
 not perform any percent-decoding.

defs.name: parse_encoded
defs.docs:
Parses a `Cookie` from the given HTTP cookie header value string where
 the name and value fields are percent-encoded. Percent-decodes the
 name/value fields.

defs.name: encoded
defs.docs:
Wraps `self` in an `EncodedCookie`: a cost-free wrapper around `Cookie`
 whose `Display` implementation percent-encodes the name and value of the
 wrapped `Cookie`.

defs.name: into_owned
defs.docs:
Converts `self` into a `Cookie` with a static lifetime. This method
 results in at most one allocation.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the name of `self`.

defs.name: value
defs.docs: Returns the value of `self`.

defs.name: name_value
defs.docs: Returns the name and value of `self` as a tuple of `(name, value)`.

defs.name: http_only
defs.docs:
Returns whether this cookie was marked `HttpOnly` or not. Returns
 `Some(true)` when the cookie was explicitly set (manually or parsed) as
 `HttpOnly`, `Some(false)` when `http_only` was manually set to `false`,
 and `None` otherwise.

defs.name: secure
defs.docs:
Returns whether this cookie was marked `Secure` or not. Returns
 `Some(true)` when the cookie was explicitly set (manually or parsed) as
 `Secure`, `Some(false)` when `secure` was manually set to `false`, and
 `None` otherwise.

defs.name: same_site
defs.docs: Returns the `SameSite` attribute of this cookie if one was specified.

defs.name: max_age
defs.docs: Returns the specified max-age of the cookie if one was specified.

defs.name: path
defs.docs: Returns the `Path` of the cookie if one was specified.

defs.name: domain
defs.docs: Returns the `Domain` of the cookie if one was specified.

defs.name: expires
defs.docs: Returns the `Expires` time of the cookie if one was specified.

defs.name: set_name
defs.docs: Sets the name of `self` to `name`.

defs.name: set_value
defs.docs: Sets the value of `self` to `value`.

defs.name: set_http_only
defs.docs: Sets the value of `http_only` in `self` to `value`.

defs.name: set_secure
defs.docs: Sets the value of `secure` in `self` to `value`.

defs.name: set_same_site
defs.docs: Sets the value of `same_site` in `self` to `value`.

defs.name: set_max_age
defs.docs: Sets the value of `max_age` in `self` to `value`.

defs.name: set_path
defs.docs: Sets the `path` of `self` to `path`.

defs.name: set_domain
defs.docs: Sets the `domain` of `self` to `domain`.

defs.name: set_expires
defs.docs: Sets the expires field of `self` to `time`.

defs.name: make_permanent
defs.docs:
Makes `self` a "permanent" cookie by extending its expiration and max
 age 20 years into the future.

defs.name: name_raw
defs.docs:
Returns the name of `self` as a string slice of the raw string `self`
 was originally parsed from. If `self` was not originally parsed from a
 raw string, returns `None`.

defs.name: value_raw
defs.docs:
Returns the value of `self` as a string slice of the raw string `self`
 was originally parsed from. If `self` was not originally parsed from a
 raw string, returns `None`.

defs.name: path_raw
defs.docs:
Returns the `Path` of `self` as a string slice of the raw string `self`
 was originally parsed from. If `self` was not originally parsed from a
 raw string, or if `self` doesn't contain a `Path`, or if the `Path` has
 changed since parsing, returns `None`.

defs.name: domain_raw
defs.docs:
Returns the `Domain` of `self` as a string slice of the raw string
 `self` was originally parsed from. If `self` was not originally parsed
 from a raw string, or if `self` doesn't contain a `Domain`, or if the
 `Domain` has changed since parsing, returns `None`.

defs.name: EncodedCookie
defs.docs:
Wrapper around `Cookie` whose `Display` implementation percent-encodes the
 cookie's name and value.
